Transport is one of the top costs incurred by Kenyans on a daily basis as they move from point to point. but with traffic jams and the high cost of transport many opt to use bodabodas which are said to be faster and more cost-effective. Bodaboda operators have however had to contend with rising fuel prices and a decline in demand due to the pandemic. Noah kipkemboi spoke to operators on the intricate balance between fuel prices and profitability.